lle marie the rbc headquarters in montreal quebec the royal bank plaza building in toronto ontario the royal centre tower in downtown vancouvers financial district tour de la banque royale in montreal quebec which housed the head office from  to  thomas darcy mcgee building rbcs office in ottawa in  the merchants bank of halifax was founded in halifax nova scotia as a commercial bank that financed the fishing and timber industries and the european and caribbean importexport businesses by  the merchants bank was officially incorporated and received its federal charter in the same year during the s and s the bank expanded into the other maritime provinces when both the newfoundland commercial bank and union bank of newfoundland collapsed on  december  the merchants bank expanded to newfoundland on  january  as the bank grew executives changed its name to reflect its growth and western expansion in  the merchants bank of halifax changed its name to the royal bank of canada rbc the centre of the canadian financial industry had moved from halifax to montreal so the merchants bank relocated its head office there in  rbc merged with the union bank of halifax in the same year it built a bank branch in winnipeg manitoba—designed by carrère and hastings in beauxarts classicism proclaiming the financial dominance of winnipeg in the prairies to improve its position in ontario rbc merged with traders bank of canada in  and in  rbc merged with quebec bank which was founded in  and chartered in  in quebec city rbcs presence in manitoba and saskatchewan was strengthened through a  merger with northern crown bank which was the result of the merger in  between northern bank established in  in winnipeg and crown bank of canada  based in ontario rbcs presence in the prairie provinces grew again with the  merger with the union bank of canada which had begun in quebec city in  as the union bank of lower canada but changed its name in  union bank of canada had moved its headquarters to winnipeg in  and had built a strong presence in the prairies in  rbc merged with crown savings and loan co merged with industrial mortgage  trust co rbc installed its first computer in  the first in canadian bankingcitation needed in the s rbc insurance was created in  it merged with ontario loan and debenture company formerly ontario savings and investment society in  rbc merged with royal trust in  rbc acquired security first network bank in atlanta—the first pure internet bank in  rbc merged merchant creditdebit card acquiring business with bmo bank of montreals to form moneris solutions in  rbc completed the acquisition of the canadian subsidiary of ally financial rbc insuranceedit rbc insurance is the largest canadian bankowned insurance organization with services to over five million people it provides life health travel home and auto and reinsurance products as well as creditor and business insurance services international expansionedit   merchants bank of halifax opened an office in bermuda   rbc opened an agency in new york city and a branch in havana   rbc bought banco de oriente de santiago de cuba by the mids rbc had  branches in cuba and is the largest bank in the country   rbc bought banco del commercio de havana   rbc opened a branch in san juan puerto rico branches in mayagüez and ponce followed   rbc established a branch in nassau bahamas   rbc opened a branch in london and acquired branches in puerto rico and port of spain trinidad as a result of its acquisition of union bank of halifax   rbc opened an agency in new york city and branches in bridgetown barbados and kingston jamaica   rbc bought bank of british honduras incorporated in  by united states citizens from mobile in british honduras which it converted to a branch rbc opened a branch in the dominican republic three more follow   rbc opened a branch in grenada   rbc bought out bank of british guiana est  in british guiana and converted it to a branch   rbc opened branches in costa rica antigu