ionalized its operations there and renamed the bank the national bank of industry and commerce ltd additionally rbc incorporated its operations in trinidad and tobago locally floating the shares thereby divesting itself of ownership the new bank took the name royal bank of trinidad and tobago rbtt   rbc sold its two branches in haiti to societe generale haitienne de banque a local bank   rbc sold its operations in belize exbritish honduras to belize holdings inc which renamed them belize bank   rbc sold royal bank of puerto rico to spains banco bilbaovizcaya   rbc sold royal trust bank austria to anglo irish bank which renamed it anglo irish bank austria   acquired dain rauscher wessels a us brokerage and investment banking firm based in minneapolis minnesota   rbc acquired centura bank based in rocky mount north carolina   rbc purchased florida interest in provident financial group cincinnati oh   rbc upgraded its representative office in beijing china to a branch   created an institutional investment joint venture with dexia the  partnership operated under the name rbc dexia investor services   rbc established a representative office in mumbai india rbc reacquired  of the shares of royal bank of trinidad and tobago this brought rbc back to trinidad and tobago some  years after it had withdrawn and provided it with a presence in other islands served by rbtt   rbc sold rbc bank to pnc financial services for us billion pnc atms are now used by customers with rbc bank georgia na providing canadians with bank options when they are residing in the us   rbc completed the acquisition of dexias percent stake in rbc dexia investor services limited making it the sole owner of the newly named rbc investor  treasury services rbc also opened a branch in wilemstad curaçao   rbc entered into a merger agreement to acquire city national corporation a major u s bank   rbc agreed to sell its swiss private bank royal bank of canada suisse sa to local rival syz group terms of the sale were not disclosed royal bank of canada suisse manages chf billion usd billion cad billion of assets for clients in africa the middle east and south america   rbc completed the acquisition of city national bank nov logoedit royal bank of canadas previous logo the crown was removed the banks symbol is a golden lion clutching a globe on a blue background an older version depicted a crown above the globe and the lion faced to the left the change coincided with an expansion in united states markets over the years the lions mane has also become less detailed and more stylized and the tongue was shortened corporate governanceedit the title of royal banks top executive has changed several times initially it was styled as president later it became chief executive officer and one often carried additional responsibilities as chairman of the board while the secondincommand was the president allan r taylor was chairman and ceo from  to  and he was succeeded by john cleghorn in that capacity from  dave mckay is currently the president and chief executive officer chief executive thomas edward kenny – herbert samuel holt – morris w wilson – sydney dobson – james muir – w earle mclaughlin – rowland c frazee – jock k finlayson – allan r taylor –  chairman and ceo – john e cleghorn –  chairman and ceo – gordon nixon –  president and ceo – gordon nixon –  ceo – david i mckay –  president  david i mckay –present  president  ceo –present chairman nonexecutive guy saintpierre – david p obrien –present history of head officesedit  merchants bank of halifax building on bedford row halifax nova scotia  four pillars building demolished except for the façade at  saint jacques street renumbered  in  montreal quebec  old royal bank building montreal at  saint jacques street montreal quebec –present place villemarie at university street  renélévesque blvd montreal quebec –present royal bank plaza at  bay street toronto ontario rbcs official legal corporate headquarters still remains at place villemarie in montreal however royal bank plaza in toronto is its de facto corporate headquarters the great majority of its management operations are based there awards and recognitionedit in  rbc was recognized as the top most  powerful brands in the world was recognized as the most respected corporation in canada in october  rbc was named one of canadas top  employers by mediacorp canada inc and was featured in macleans newsmagazine later that month rbc was also named one of greater torontos top employers which was announced by the toronto star newspaper according to a global newsweek ranking which measures how effectively companies manage environmental risks and opportunities relative to their industry peers royal bank of canada is the most environmentally friendly company in the world sponsorshipedit like many of its competitors rbc is a key sponsor of many events community programs and charities one percent of rbcs average annual net income before taxes is set aside for charitable partnerships via the armslength rbc foundation rbc is a major sponsor of numerous cultural events including the toronto international film festival it also sponsors the rbc taylor prize a literary award for nonfiction writing in canada and hosts a yearly canadian women entrepreneur award in july  the rbc foundation partnered with the university of toronto to revive the siminovitch prize in theatre given to recognize achievement in canadian theatre rbc is one of canadas largest sponsors of amateur sports and is the longestrunning canadian sponsor of the olympic games it employ dozens of toptier amateur athletes as parttime spokespeople through the rbc olympians program rbc is also a major sponsor of hockey canada and owns the naming rights to the canadian national junior a ice hockey championship the royal bank cup in addition it supports canadian hockey at the grassroots level through the rbc play hockey program rbc owns naming rights to the rbc centre rbc convention centre winnipeg rbc canadian open and rbc heritage formerly the heritage classic from  to  rbc previously held the naming rights to what is now the pnc arena in raleigh north carolina controversiesedit mergeredit in  the royal bank of canada proposed to merge with the bank of montreal at the same time as the torontodominion bank proposed to merge with the canadian imperial bank of commerce both mergers were examined by the competition bureau of canada and ultimately rejected by paul martin at the time the finance minister of canada and future prime minister discriminationedit on january   cbc radio reported rbc is refusing people of certain nationalities to open us dollar accounts with the bank canadian citizens with dual citizenship in cuba iran iraq myanmar north korea or sudan mostly countries with us sanctions are affected the us treasury department restricts certain foreign nationals from using the us dollar payment system to limit terrorism and money laundering after the september   attacks rbc replied that compliance with such laws does not represent an endorsement by the bank and on january  clarified its position on the application of the us laws specifying that with some exceptions it does open accounts for dual citizens of the sanctioned countries there have also been reports that the bank has closed the accounts of some iraniancanadian citizens environmentedit environmental groups have criticized rbcs financing of oil sands bitumen extraction and expansion cumulatively issuing more than  billion in loans and financing more than  billion in corporate debt between  and  for  companies including encana husky energy opti canada delphi energy canadian oil sands trust northwest upgrading suncor total connacher oil and gas interpipeline and enbridge some environmental groups believe oil sands extraction has a detrimental effect on the northern alberta environment  ottawa branch firebombingedit an rbc branch in the glebe neighbourhood of ottawa was firebombed in may  the party responsible later identified themselves on indymedia and threatened to make their presence at the upcoming  winter olympics in vancouver as rbc was one of its key sponsors as well as at the  g toronto summit temporary foreign workers and canadian layoffsedit main article temporary foreign worker program in canada see also amanda lang rbc controversy in april  the cbc reported that the royal bank of canada was indirectly hiring temporary foreign workers to replace  canadian information technology workers the cbc reported may   that during question period the ndp leveled accusations against the government and that prime minister stephen harper responded that the government has been working on problems with the temporary foreign worker program for more than a year membershipsedit rbc is a member of the canadian bankers association cba and is a registered member with the canada deposit insurance corporation cdic a federal agency insuring deposits at all of canadas chartered banks it is also a member of carifs atm network interac mastercard in the caribbean markets and beginning in march  in canada nyce point of sale network plus network global banking alliance for women galleryedit an rbc building in richmond hill ontario royal bank building in winnipeg manitoba a branch of the rbc bank in holetown barbados rbc tower in vancouver royal bank of canada branch left and parliament of barbados the rbcs office in montreal at the place villemarie see alsoedit companies portal the union bank robberies of  and  list of investors in bernard l madoff securities referencesedit  mcdowall  inlay  a b yusufali sasha  december  royal bank of canada the canadian encyclopedia retrieved august     rbc ousts torontodominion to become canada’s top bank as both hit  trillion milestone financial post retrieved  february    a b royal bank of canada annual report  pdf rbc  october  retrieved august     about rbc bank company profile rbcbankusacom retrieved    royal bank of canada annual report  pdf