a million customers rbc also has  branches across seventeen countries in the caribbean which serve more than  million clients rbc capital markets is rbcs worldwide investment and corporate banking subsidiary while the investment brokerage firm is known as rbc dominion securities investment banking services are also provided through rbc bank and the focus is on middle market clients in  rbc was the largest canadian company by revenue and market capitalization and was ranked at  in the  forbes global  listing the company has operations in canada and  other countries and had us billion of assets under management in  contents  history  rbc insurance  international expansion  logo  corporate governance  history of head offices  awards and recognition  sponsorship  controversies  merger  discrimination  environment   ottawa branch firebombing  temporary foreign workers and canadian layoffs  memberships  gallery  see also  references  further reading  external links  official sites historyedit this article is in a list format that may be better presented using prose you can help by converting this article to prose if appropriate editing help is available january  place ville marie the rbc headquarters in montreal quebec the royal bank plaza building in toronto ontario the royal centre tower in downtown vancouvers financial district tour de la banque royale in montreal quebec which housed the head office from  to  thomas darcy mcgee building rbcs office in ottawa in  the merchants bank of halifax was founded in halifax nova scotia as a commercial bank that financed the fishing and timber industries and the european and caribbean importexport businesses by  the merchants bank was officially incorporated and received its federal charter in the same year during the s and s the bank expanded into the other maritime provinces when both the newfoundland commercial bank and union bank of newfoundland collapsed on  december  the merchants bank expanded to newfoundland on  january  as the bank grew executives changed its name to reflect its growth and western expansion in  the merchants bank of halifax changed its name to the royal bank of canada rbc the centre of the canadian financial industry had moved from halifax to montreal so the merchants bank relocated its head office there in  rbc merged with the union bank of halifax in the same year it built a bank branch in winnipeg manitoba—designed by carrère and hastings in beauxarts classicism proclaiming the financial dominance of winnipeg in the prairies to improve its position in ontario rbc merged with traders bank of canada in  and in  rbc merged with quebec bank which was founded in  and chartered in  in quebec city rbcs presence in manitoba and saskatchewan was strengthened through a  merger with northern crown bank which was the result of the merger in  between northern bank established in  in winnipeg and crown bank of canada  based in ontario rbcs presence in the prairie provinces grew again with the  merger with the union bank of canada which had begun in quebec city in  as the union bank of lower canada but changed its name in  union bank of canada had moved its headquarters to winnipeg in  and had built a strong presence in the prairies in  rbc merged with crown savings and loan co merged with industrial mortgage  trust co rbc installed its first computer in  the first in canadian bankingcitation needed in the s rbc insurance was created in  it merged with ontario loan and debenture company formerly ontario savings and investment society in  rbc merged with royal trust in  rbc acquired security first network bank in atlanta—the first pure internet bank in  rbc merged merchant creditdebit card acquiring business with bmo bank of montreals to form moneris solutions in  rbc completed the acquisition of the canadian subsidiary of ally financial rbc insuranceedit rbc insurance is the largest canadian bankowned insurance organization with services to over five million people it provides life health travel home and auto and reinsurance products as well as creditor and business insurance services international expansionedit   merchants bank of halifax opened an office in bermuda   rbc opened an agency in new york city and a branch in havana   rbc bought banco de oriente de santiago de cuba by the mids rbc had  branches in cuba and is the largest bank in the country   rbc bought banco del commercio de havana   rbc opened a branch in san juan puerto rico branches in mayagüez and ponce followed   rbc established a branch in nassau bahamas   rbc opened a branch in london and acquired branches in puerto rico and port of spain trinidad as a result of its acquisition of union bank of halifax   rbc opened an agency in new york city and branches in bridgetown barbados and kingston jamaica   rbc bought bank of british honduras incorporated in  by united states citizens from mobile in british honduras which it converted to a branch rbc opened a branch in the dominican republic three more follow   rbc opened a branch in grenada   rbc bought out bank of british guiana est  in british guiana and converted it to a branch   rbc opened branches in costa rica antigua dominica and st kitts   rbc opened a branch in venezuela   rbc opened branches in antigua dominica st kitts montserrat nevis and tobago   rbc opened a branch in barcelona and another in vladivostok that lasted less than a year   rbc opened branches in brazil argentina uruguay paris martinique guadaloupe and portauprince haiti   rbc opened a branch in colombia and a branch in castries st lucia   rbc bought and consolidated the banking operations of pedro gomez mena e hijo in cuba   rbc opened a branch in peru and acquired the americanowned and failed bank of central and south america the purchase of bcsa brought with it subsidiaries and their branches in colombia costa rica peru and venezuela   rbc closed its branch in st lucia   rbc closed its branches in martinique and guadaloupe   rbc opened a branch in st vincent   rbc returned to st lucia   fidel castros regime acquired the rbcs operations in cuba on  december at the time of the forced sale rbc had  branches in cuba from  to  rbc maintained a special representative in havana to facilitate trade between cuba and canada actually the special representatives primary function after the failed bay of pigs invasion in april  was to act as a financial intermediary between the american and cuban governments to manage the ransoming of the prisoners for food and agricultural machinery   rbc opened a branch in george town grand cayman s  as a result of law  rbcs operations in colombia became banco royal colombiano   rbc was forced to incorporate its operations in jamaica which became royal bank jamaica   rbc purchased banco de san juan in puerto rico adding its  branches to the six that rbc already had in puerto rico rbc sold to republic bank of trinidad and tobago its assets in grenada   rbc started to withdraw from much of the caribbean it sold its  branches in the dominican republic to banco de comercio dominicano it also sold its stake in royal bank jamaica to jamaica mutual life assurance the government of guyana nationalized its operations there and renamed the bank the national bank of industry and commerce ltd additionally rbc incorporated its operations in trinidad and tobago locally floating the shares thereby divesting itself of ownership the new bank took the name royal bank of trinidad and tobago rbtt   rbc sold its two branches in haiti to societe generale haitienne de banque a local bank   rbc sold its operations in belize exbritish honduras to belize holdings inc which renamed them belize bank   rbc sold royal bank of puerto rico to spains banco bilbaovizcaya   rbc sold royal trust bank austria to anglo irish bank which renamed it anglo irish bank austria   acquired dain rauscher wessels a us brokerage and investment banking firm based in minneapolis minnesota   rbc acquired centura bank based in rocky mount north carolina   rbc purchased florida interest in provident financial group cincinnati oh   rbc upgraded its representative office in beijing china to a branch   created an institutional investment joint venture with dexia the  partnership operated under the name rbc dexia investor services   rbc established a representative office in mumbai india rbc reacquired  of the shares of royal bank of trinidad and tobago this brought rbc back to trinidad and tobago some  years after it had withdrawn and provided it with a presence in other islands served by rbtt   rbc sold rbc bank to pnc financial services for us billion pnc atms are now used by customers with rbc bank georgia na providing canadians with bank options when they are residing in the us   rbc completed the acquisition of dexias percent stake in rbc dexia investor services limited making it the sole owner of the newly named rbc investor  treasury services rbc also opened a branch in wilemstad curaçao   rbc entered into a merger agreement to acquire city national corporation a major u s bank   rbc agreed to sell its swiss private bank royal bank of canada suisse sa to local rival syz group terms of the sale were not disclosed royal bank of canada suisse manages chf billion usd billion cad billion of assets for clients in africa the middle east and south america   rbc completed the acquisition of city national bank nov logoedit royal bank of canadas previous logo the crown was removed the banks symbol is a golden lion clutching a globe on a blue background an older version depicted a crown above the globe and the lion faced to the left the change coincided with an expansion in united states markets over the years the lions mane has also become less detailed and more stylized and the tongue was shortened corporate governanceedit the title of royal banks top executive has changed several times initially it was styled as president later it became chief executive officer and one often carried additional responsibilities as chairman of the board while the secondincommand was the president allan r taylor was chairman and ceo from  to  and he was succeeded by john cleghorn in that capacity from  dave mckay is currently the president and chief executive officer chief executive thomas edward kenny – herbert samuel holt – morris w wilson – sydney dobson – james muir – w earle mclaughlin – rowland c frazee – jock k finlayson – allan r taylor –  chairman and ceo – john e cleghorn –  chairman and ceo – gordon nixon –  president and ceo – gordon nixon –  ceo – david i mckay –  president  david i mckay –present  president  ceo –present chairman nonexecutive guy saintpierre – david p obrien –present history of head officesedit  merchants bank of halifax building on bedford row halifax nova scotia  four pillars building demolished except for the façade at  saint jacques street renumbered  in  montreal quebec  old royal bank building montreal at  saint jacques street montreal quebec –present place villemarie at university street  renélévesque blvd montreal quebec –present royal bank plaza at  bay street toronto ontario rbcs official legal corporate headquarters still remains at place villemarie in montreal however royal bank plaza in toronto is its de facto corporate headquarters the great majority of its management operations are based there awards and recognitionedit in  rbc was recognized as the top most  powerful brands in the world was recognized as the most respected corporation in canada in october  rbc was named one of canadas top  employers by mediacorp canada inc and was featured in macleans newsmagazine later that month rbc was also named one of greater torontos top employers which was announced by the toronto star newspaper according to a global newsweek ranking which measures how effectively companies manage environmental risks and opportunities relative to their industry peers royal bank of canada is the most environmentally friendly company in the world sponsorshipedit like many of its competitors rbc is a key sponsor of many events community programs and charities one percent of rbcs average annual net income before taxes is set aside for charitable partnerships via the armslength rbc foundation rbc is a major sponsor of numerous cultural events including the toronto international film festival it also sponsors the rbc taylor prize a literary award for nonfiction writing in canada and hosts a yearly canadian women entrepreneur award in july  the rbc foundation partnered with the university of toronto to revive the siminovitch prize in theatre given to recognize achievement in canadian theatre rbc is one of canadas largest sponsors of amateur sports and is the longestrunning canadian sponsor of the olympic games it employ dozens of toptier amateur athletes as parttime spokespeople through the rbc olympians program rbc is also a major sponsor of hockey canada and owns the naming rights to the canadian national junior a ice hockey championship the royal bank cup in addition it supports canadian hockey at the grassroots level through the rbc play hockey program rbc owns naming rights to the rbc centre rbc convention centre winnipeg rbc canadian open and rbc heritage formerly the heritage classic from  to  rbc previously held the naming rights to what is now the pnc arena in raleigh north carolina controversiesedit mergeredit in  the royal bank of canada proposed to merge with the bank of montreal at the same time as the torontodominion bank proposed to merge with the canadian imperial bank of commerce both mergers were examined by the competition bureau of canada and ultimately rejected by paul martin at the time the finance minister of canada and future prime minister discriminationedit on january   cbc radio reported rbc is refusing people of certain nationalities to open us dollar accounts with the bank canadian citizens with dual citizenship in cuba iran iraq myanmar north korea or sudan mostly countries with us sanctions are affected the us treasury department restricts certain foreign nationals from using the us dollar payment system to limit terrorism and money laundering after the september   attacks rbc replied that compliance with such laws does not represent an endorsement by the bank and on january  clarified its position on the application of the us laws specifying that with some exceptions it does open accounts for dual citizens of the sanctioned countries there have also been reports that the bank has closed the accounts of some iraniancanadian citizens environmentedit environmental groups have criticized rbcs financing of oil sands bitumen extraction and expansion cumulatively issuing more than  billion in loans and financing more than  billion in corporate debt between  and  for  companies including encana husky energy opti canada delphi energy canadian oil sands trust northwest upgrading suncor total connacher oil and gas interpipeline and enbridge some environmental groups believe oil sands extraction has a detrimental effect on the northern alberta environment  ottawa branch firebombingedit an rbc branch in the glebe neighbourhood of ottawa was firebombed in may  the party responsible later identified themselves on indymedia and threatened to make their presence at the upcoming  winter olympics in vancouver as rbc was one of its key sponsors as well as at the  g toronto summit temporary foreign workers and canadian layoffsedit main article temporary foreign worker program in canada see also amanda lang rbc controversy in april  the cbc reported that the royal bank of canada was indirectly hiring temporary foreign workers to replace  canadian information technology workers the cbc reported may   that during question period the ndp leveled accusations against the government and that prime minister stephen harper responded that the government has been working on problems with the temporary foreign worker program for more than a year membershipsedit rbc is a member of the canadian bankers association cba and is a registered member with the canada deposit insurance corporation cdic a federal agency insuring deposits at all of canadas chartered banks it is also a member of carifs atm network interac mastercard in the caribbean markets and beginning in march  in canada nyce point of sale network plus network global banking alliance for women galleryedit an rbc building in richmond hill ontario royal bank building in winnipeg manitoba a branch of the rbc bank in holetown barbados rbc tower in vancouver royal bank of canada branch left and parliament of barbados the rbcs office in montreal at the place villemarie see alsoedit companies portal the union bank robberies of  and  list of investors in bernard l madoff securities referencesedit  mcdowall  inlay  a b yusufali sasha  december  royal bank of canada the canadian encyclopedia retrieved august     rbc ousts torontodominion to become canada’s top bank as both hit  trillion milestone financial post retrieved  february    a b royal bank of canada annual report  pdf rbc  october  retrieved august     about rbc bank company profile rbcbankusacom retrieved    royal bank of canada annual report  pdf rbc  october  retrieved august     canadas  biggest companies by market cap the globe and mail toronto theglobeandmailcom  june  retrieved august     the global  forbes  april  retrieved august     corporate profile rbc retrieved    global private banking benchmark   scorpio report scorpiopartnershipcom  retrieved    a b c d rbc insurance history  retrieved  march    a b c pound richard w  fitzhenry and whiteside book of canadian facts and dates fitzhenry and whiteside   kalman harold d vattay sharon  december  bank architecture the canadian encyclopedia toronto historica foundation retrieved august     nineteenth legislature  ontario sessional papers pdf p iii ol m   brock daniel j  jeffery joseph in halpenny francess g dictionary of canadian biography xii – online ed university of toronto press   jordan